==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Edgy
<hw>Edg"y</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[From
<er>Edge</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Easily irritated; sharp; <as>as,
an <ex>edgy</ex> temper</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Fine Arts)</fld> <def>Having some of the forms,
such as drapery or the like, too sharply defined.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧An
<xex>edgy</xex> style of sculpture.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Hazlitt.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Edh</ent>⟦br⟧
